content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #90101 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
It's not a major diagnostics regression but apparently incorrect, so P-medium would be fine
I see you marked this as regression-from-stable-to-stable. The current stable does not seem to have this bug, so is this a regression in 1.56.0 (being released tomorrow)?
Ah, no, I tested it on playground and didn't know beta channel is already 1.57 (I thought it was 1.56). The bug should be introduced by #88719 so it should've been from-stable-to-beta.
I would say this can be quite confusing for users, and is ideally fixed before release, so maybe we can use P-high to keep track.
I'm fine either way :+1:

I agree with Gary Guo, this seems like P-high, not P-medium. The error is actively misleading about which part of the code has an issue. The old error was also confusing, but at least it wasn't fully incorrect.
